                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">not condoning this at all, and going on the record saying its a bad idea... but an escrow would work like this
<br />

<br />

<br />
player1 makes arrangements with player2 to sell leetitem_01
<br />

<br />
player1 goes to sony website and pays 1 dollar, and marks the item from his inventory
<br />

<br />
player2 then goes to sony website and pays 1 dollar, and marks from a list of items he can retrieve
<br />

<br />
Sony then automatically moves the items from player1 to player2, and collects 2 dollars. (they may add in a true money escrow like paypal to this IF they did go ahead with this plan)
<br />
---------------------------------
<br />

<br />
This would set off so much hassle, especially people selling stuff xserver, and then people stripping accounts etc, as to damage the integrity of server economies.
<br />

<br />
The plus side for the consumer is that its secure
<br />

<br />
the other plus side, is that this could put Yantis and friends out of business as far as items go, or at least put a sizeable dent in their profit margin, and when it comes to dealing with other big companies, thats the only place to make it hurt.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=259328" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.therunes.net/forums/files/nanyea.gif" border="0" /></a>
<br />
<span style="color: cyan">EQ2 Area Moderator</span>
<br />
<a href="http://www.TheRunes.Net" target="_blank">www.TheRunes.Net</a>
<br />

<br />
