                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This sounds to me like Sony's thinking about collecting a nice transaction fee for itself in taking over Yantis's business.  Sony already stated they had collected over $1 million in character transfer fees.  They probably see this as a gold mine if they collected a rl money fee on it.
<br />

<br />
Yes, Yantis does it, and many people already buy characters and items in rl money.  But to do this officially means there will be all kinds of money-hungry sharks out farming where our regular adventure zones are.  It will totally ruin our fantasy gaming atmosphere and turn it into a rl money farm.
<br />

<br />
In real life I can afford to buy items and characters, but I never do it because I'd like to earn it in game.  I come to this game to feel the struggle of money.  Sadly, if this is implemented I'll be watching hordes of sellers ruining my hunting zones.
<br />

<br />
My one alternative would be to pluck down rl money.  The game can then turn into a "who is rich in rl" contest.  I used to play an old text MUD called Gemstone 3 where top players paid $3000 rl money for a sword.  EQ will become a game for the rich.  Heh, we can even start selling KEI for rl money.
